 Wednesday, June 24, 1998      The Hearst News Service will file the following stories for
Thursday. If you have questions, call Tim Spence at 202-298-6920.  
    (Slugline includes the ``HNS'' tag.)
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-INITIATIVES (San Francisco) _ California voters will be
asked once again to be legislators this November, deciding on
ballot measures on Indian gambling, tax credits to reduce air
pollution, and even a ban on the sale of horses for human
consumption. By ZACHARY COILE.
