suffer from tinnitus, a ringing in the ears. It isn't a disease.
It's a symptom that can be caused by exposure to loud noise, high
blood pressure, allergies and chronic use of certain medications.
By SYLVIA WOOD.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-REAX (San Francisco) _ While politicians and pundits
debate President Clinton's historic trip to China, many local
Chinese Americans view the visit as a matter of pride. By JULIE
CHAO.
