<P>
   ATT-TCI-IMPACT _ The impact of the ATT/TCI merger on the future
of broadband. Could this alliance force other media companies to
rush broadband to market? (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ATT-TCI-ANTRUST _ What are the anti-trust implications in the
AT&AMP;T/TCI deal? And what political and legal climate will it face
from regulators in Washington. (Dart, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   ATT-TCI-HOLSEN _ Ever since AT&AMP;T was dismembered nearly 15 years
ago, it has been searching for an identity. Whether to become big
and dominant again, whether to fashion itself into the ultimate
wireless phone company, or perhaps to reassemble a new millenium
version of Ma Bell, combining long distance and local service. Each
idea was tried, examined or pondered and found wanting. AT&AMP;T had
lost its soul irretrievably it seemed, mostly because its smartest
managers had been dispersed among the regionals and other
enterprises. Now, finally, it seems that AT&AMP;T has found the right
partner, a highly directed dreamer named John Malone, whose simple
idea is to pour the world of information into homes. With Malone's
ideas and dreams, and the wealth name brand of AT&AMP;T, it seems that
the new combination can set a pace for the huge telecommunications
industry. Clearly, the possibility has riveted the attention of all
the players. (Holsendolph, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HAYESS _ Hayes Corp. on Wednesday announced dramatic
restructuring that includes a rewritten financial arrangement and a
new chief financial officer. (Husted, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MICROS _ Now that the federal appeals court has ruled in favor
of Microsoft, how does that effect the current anti-trust
litigation? Also has the anti-trust atmosphere in Washington been
changed by Tuesday's ruling. (Dart, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   DELTA _ Delta and United are talking about accelerating the
first element of their planned alliance, the merger of frequent
flier programs. They've notified their pilot unions of the step.
(Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   25ASPEN _ Regional airline stops Austin service. Roundup of
whose left in regional service. (Breyer, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   25WINDOWS _ Windows 98 goes on sale. Local retailers do crazy
stuff. (Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   25WITI _ Carol Bartz, CEO of Autodesk, gives the keynote address
to the Women in Technology International Conference in Santa Clara,
Calif. (Hawkins, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
