<P>
   HEALTH-BRIEFS _ An analysis of a 1996 outbreak of multi-drug
resistant pneumonia in an Okla. nursing home (11 sickened, 3 dead)
says that it's vital that the institutionalized elderly be
vaccinated; some patients with epilepsy can have clusters of
repeated seizures that are different from their regular pattern of
seizures and that last hours and a drug-containing gel that's
administered rectally seems to be effective, safe and inexpensive.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
