<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MAVENS-FASHION-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHE DARED TO BE DIFFERENT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BARBARA DE WITT 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ &UR;  &LR; Image is everything.
</P>
<P>
   Jackie Kennedy proved it with her matching dress-and-coat
ensembles and those little pill box hats. Grace Kelly had so much
fashion clout that the style of her Hermes handbag is now referred
to as the ``Kelly bag.''
</P>
<P>
   The late Princess Diana had the same power. Everything she wore,
from her wedding gown to her frisky haircut to her Christian Dior
purse, made fashion headlines. In honor of her birthday on July 1,
we asked a few fashion mavens to tell us what they liked best about
the royal fashion icon.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Mr. Blackwell, fashion arbiter &LR;  _ &UR;  &LR; ``She was a great fashion
independent. It wasn't only her sense of style, but her ability to
carry the style with grace and elegance, and project true royalty,
that made her an icon.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Anne Cole, L.A. swimwear designer _ &LR;  ``She was the very
portrait of ladylike sensibility ... and I was honored to know she
once ordered a swimsuit from my Anne Cole Collection. It was a
classic plaid high-neck maillot.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Frederic Fekkai, hairdresser &LR;   &UR; to &LR;   &UR; the &LR;   &UR; stars _  &LR; ``She'll be
best-remembered for her striking suits, and, of course, her
always-modern hairstyles. I think her last style was perhaps her
most flattering. It was certainly sexy.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Milinda Martin &LR; , &UR; Robinsons-May spokeswoman _  &LR; ``Unlike the
other members of the royal family, she broke fashion rules ... like
wearing a necklace as a headband.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Judy Rabineau, designer for Mica fashions _  &LR; ``The
off-the-shoulder dress with the brooch _ the one like Celine Dion
wore to the Oscars _ and that purse with the charms on it by
Christian Dior ... wow. She now marches with the likes of Jackie
Kennedy.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Denise Filchner,  &LR; a &UR; ccessories fashion director for Macy's _
 &LR; ``Princess Diana did more for the world of fine jewelry than
anyone has for a long time. She brought public awareness to
sapphires, starting from her wedding day. And her signature
diamond-and-sapphire necklace was copied by numerous costume
jewelry designers such as Carolee so we all could have that royal
look.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Alanna Chaffin, spokeswoman for the CaliforniaMart _
 &LR; ``Princess Diana was a contemporary thinker who wasn't afraid to
wear red or bold patterns, even though they probably weren't in the
royal dress code.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; David Dart, L.A. fashion designer _  &LR; ``She wore the clothes ...
they didn't wear her. Whether it was a finely tailored suit or
glamorous evening gown, I was always amazed at how comfortable she
looked.''
</P>
</TEXT>
