<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MORGAN-CATERER-1700(2TAKES)-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BET MARTHA STEWART DOESN'T KNOW HER CATERER HAILS FROM WICHITA
FALLS, TEXAS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED: calories from fat. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DEVIL'S FOOD CAKE WITH MARSHMALLOW FROSTING
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   Solid vegetable shortening, for the pans
</P>
<P>
   1 3/4 cups unbleached all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   1 3/4 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup sifted unsweetened cocoa powder
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoon baking powder
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoon baking soda
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   2 cups milk
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   3 large eggs, lightly beaten
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   Marshmallow frosting, recipe follows
</P>
<P>
   2 cups coconut chips, optional
</P>
<P>
   Position a rack in the middle of the oven and preheat to 350
degrees. Lightly coat two 8-inch round cake pans with shortening.
Line the pans with parchment or waxed paper.
</P>
<P>
   Into a large bowl, sift together twice the flour, sugar, cocoa,
baking powder, baking soda and salt. Gradually mix in the milk,
oil, eggs and vanilla. Stir until moistened. Do not over mix.
Divide the batter evenly between the prepared pans.
</P>
<P>
   Bake until cakes are just pulling away from the sides of the
pans and their tops spring back when lightly pressed, about 30
minutes. Cool in the pans on the rack for 10 minutes. Remove from
the pans, peel off the parchment and cool on racks to room
temperature.
</P>
<P>
   Set 1 layer on a cake plate. Spread about one-third of the
frosting over the layer. Scatter about 3/4 cup of the coconut chips
(if desired) over the frosting. Set the second layer in place.
Frost the cake all over with the remaining frosting. Scatter
remaining coconut chips over the cake (press some into the sides,
as well, if desired)
</P>
<P>
   The layers can be baked up to 1 day in advance (wrap the layer
separately in plastic wrap and refrigerate), but the cake should be
served within an hour of frosting.
</P>
<P>
   Cut the cake into wedges for serving.
</P>
<P>
   Note: For cupcakes, divide the batter among 20 greased muffin
cups (fill each no more than two-thirds full). Bake until puffed
and just pulling away from the sides of the muffin tins, 12-15
minutes. Cool slightly, then remove from the pan and cool
completely. Frost with marshmallow frosting and top with coconut
chips, if desired, or use your favorite chocolate frosting and top
with coconut chips, if desired, or use your favorite chocolate
icing.
</P>
<P>
   Marshmallow frosting:
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons water
</P>
<P>
   2 large egg whites
</P>
<P>
   1 (7-ounce) jar marshmallow creme
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon almond extract
</P>
<P>
   In the top of the double boiler set over simmering water, beat
together the sugar, water and egg whites until soft peaks form. Add
the marshmallow creme and heat until stiff peaks form. Remove from
heat and beat in the almond extract.
</P>
<P>
   Use immediately or cover and refrigerate overnight.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving with coconut chips: 675
calories, 25 grams fat, 106 grams carbohydrates, 12 grams protein,
128 milligrams cholesterol, 531 milligrams sodium, 33 percent of
calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
