   CHINA-CLINTON _ XIAN, China _ With the whole world watching, the
nine days that may make or break
</P>
<P>
   Bill Clinton's presidency are starting to unfold on Thursday to
the sound of Chinese gongs. ``Future historians will measure
Clinton's every step in China to gauge whether this is a journey
into greatness or a lame duck's descent into mediocracy.'' ``So
far, what is startling is that so little about the final outcome of
</P>
<P>
   the summit is predetermined, even as the Chinese unfurl a carpet
as long as two football fields to greet the first American
president to China in nine years. (Albright, Kunstel , Cox News
Service).
