   ENDICOTT _ Q&AMP;A with John Endicott, a Georigia Tech expert on
Asian security issues. He speaks Thursday night at a Georgia
Council for International Visitors program. (Melvin, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   XINAN _ Xi'an, China _ I am home. From the descending airplane I
can see the loess-covered landscape of the Yellow Earth Plateau,
winding up and down. As we approach, I see the city wall and moat,
ringing Xi'an in brick and water. In many of my homesick dreams in
the States, Xi'an stayed as still and as solid as the
thousand-year-old stone city wall. But I would return to find a
much different Xi'an, just as Xi'an would find a much different me.
Story by Liu Xin. (Palm Beach Post)
</P>
