<SLUG> BC-GLF-CADILLAC-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CADILLAC NFL CLASSIC SHOWS OFF ANOTHER QUALITY COURSE IN NEW
JERSEY
</HEADLINE>
   (ja) 
 By DAVE ANDERSON    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLIFTON, N.J. _ Whenever George Steinbrenner complains about
Yankee Stadium, the Yankees' principal owner hints at how New
Jersey will be the team's new home even though no plans exist for a
ball park in the Garden State.
</P>
<P>
   But if the Yankees were a golf team, they could move tomorrow.
Whenever a golf ``stadium,'' so to speak, is needed for a tour
event, New Jersey has more than enough quality courses.
</P>
<P>
   During the Cadillac NFL Classic that starts here Thursday at the
Upper Montclair Country Club, spectators not only will be in the
galleries on the course but also on the balconies of the adjacent
high-rise apartments just as they were 36 years ago. And the
primary object of their affection will be the same man.
</P>
<P>
   Arnold Palmer is his name. Then, as now, golf is his game.
</P>
<P>
   When he teed off here in the Thunderbird Classic in 1962, the
then 32-year-old touring pro out of Latrobe, Pa., was the golfer
who would be known as the King, the golfer everybody wanted to see.
Two months earlier he had won his third Masters and later that
summer he would win his second consecutive British Open.
</P>
<P>
   When he tees off in this weekend's Senior PGA Tour event at
Upper Montclair, he will still be the King, the golfer everybody
still wants to see.
</P>
<P>
   Now 68, Palmer is basically the same golfer he has always been.
He still lunges at the ball. He still hitches up his pants. After a
birdie, his smile is still brighter than the sunshine. In his way,
he is as enduring as any quality golf course.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking of quality golf courses, near Atlantic City, the
ShopRite Classic on the Ladies Professional Golf Association tour
will begin Thursday on the Bay course at the Seaview Marriott
resort. Sam Snead won the Professional Golfers' Association
championship there in 1942.
</P>
<P>
   Courses like this don't get older, they just get better.
Especially New Jersey's classic courses, where so many classic
golfers have won.
</P>
<P>
   Over the years, Baltusrol, in nearby Springfield, has been the
site of a record-sharing seven U.S. Open championships, two won by
Jack Nicklaus in 1967 and 1980. It twice was the host club for the
U.S. Women's Open, won by Mickey Wright in 1961 and Kathy Baker in
1985.
</P>
<P>
   Pine Valley, secluded in Clementon not too far from Atlantic
City, has been No. 1 in Golf Digest magazine's ranking of America's
100 Greatest Courses for more than a decade. Baltusrol's Lower
course is No. 28.
</P>
<P>
   Plainfield Country Club, where Laura Davies won the 1987 U.S.
Women's Open and John Cook won the 1978 U.S. Amateur, is ranked No.
39 in the nation. Somerset Hills C.C., in Bernardsville, where the
1990 Curtis Cup matches were held, is No. 43.
</P>
<P>
   In Golf Digest's state-by-state rankings, Pine Valley,
Baltusrol's Lower course, Plainfield and Somerset Hills were New
Jersey's top four, in that order. Baltusrol's Upper course was
fifth.
</P>
<P>
   Ridgewood Country Club, the site of the 1990 U.S. Senior Open
duel in which Lee Trevino edged Nicklaus, and the 1935 Ryder Cup
matches, was sixth on Golf Digest's state list. Galloway National
was seventh. Metedeconk was eighth.
</P>
<P>
   Upper Montclair, where the Garden State Parkway crosses Route 3,
has been the site of the most New Jersey events, 14, on the three
pro tours _ the PGA Tour, the Senior PGA Tour and the LPGA tour.
</P>
<P>
   Bob Murphy has won at Upper Montclar on two tours. He won the
1968 Thunderbird on the PGA Tour and the 1996 Cadillac NFL Classic
on the Senior PGA Tour.
</P>
<P>
   This will be Upper Montclair's sixth Cadillac NFL Classic,
featuring a separate division for pro football players. It also has
had five PGA Tour events _ four Thunderbird Classics in 1962, 1966,
1967 (when Palmer won) and 1968, plus the 1970 Dow Jones Open (won
by Bobby Nichols).
</P>
<P>
   In the four LPGA events here, the Coca-Cola Classic was won by
Nancy Lopez in 1979 and Donna White in 1980; the Chrysler-Plymouth
Classic by Pat Bradley in 1983 and Barb Bunkowsky in 1984.
</P>
<P>
   In the years to come, Upper Montclair, along with a few other
New Jersey courses such as Baltusrol and Ridgewood, will be able to
put up a sign that every golf fan will cherish. Quite simply, all
that sign needs to say is, ``Arnold Palmer played here.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
