<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Hats to watches: Patriotic fever colors fashions
 &HT;    (EMBARGOED UNTIL JUNE 28: DO NOT USE BEFORE THEN)
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Whether you run a marathon or sun yourself at the pool this July
Fourth, celebrate your fashion independence in patriotic colors.
</P>
<P>
   White, red and blue are never out of fashion, but this time of
the year, they are definitely in.
</P>
<P>
   ``As Americans, we feel good in these colors,'' says Margaret
Walch of the Color Association of the United States. ``They are
clean, practical and forthright _ everything for which we stand.
</P>
<P>
   ``And we seem to be more comfortable in these less complicated
shades than say a raspberry or a chartreuse.''
</P>
<P>
   Get into the spirit with head-to-toe items ranging from
red-and-white bikinis and tri-colored athletic shoes to
star-studded T-shirts, baseball caps and Americana jewelry.
Patriotic fever also runs to watches. Swatch always includes
several summer styles in red, white or blue, according to company
representative Trish O'Callahan because ``these are the colors of
several national flags and consistently good sellers.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
