   CONGRESS-HEALTH (Washington) _ House Republicans unveil a
long-awaited proposal to define patients' rights and set uniform
nationwide standards for health insurance, especially HMOs. The
health insurance industry immediately denounces the proposal,
saying it will increase costs for consumers. By Robert Pear.
(Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   AT&AMP;T-TCI (Undated) _ AT&AMP;T Corp., the nation's largest telephone
