<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-MATCHUP-SPOILED-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SILVER CHARM'S FEVER SPOILS DREAM RACE
</HEADLINE>
   (ja) 
 By JAY PRIVMAN   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The anticipated matchup between the nation's three best older
horses has been postponed yet again. Silver Charm, last year's
champion 3-year-old colt and the Kentucky Derby winner, Wednesday
morning was declared out of Sunday's $1 million Hollywood Gold Cup
because he came down with a slight fever, according to his trainer,
Bob Baffert.
</P>
<P>
   Silver Charm's withdrawal prevents him from meeting Skip Away
and Gentlemen for the first time. Gentlemen and Skip Away have met
once previously _ when Gentlemen captured last year's Pimlico
Special _ but Hollywood Park management was hoping to be the first
to get all three in the same race.
</P>
<P>
   Baffert said Silver Charm had a temperature of 102 degrees _ two
degrees above normal for a horse _ Wednesday morning in his stall
at Santa Anita. The colt had worked out at Santa Anita on Tuesday
morning, just two days after returning from Kentucky, where he
raced 12 days ago.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's got something there, so we can't afford to take a
chance,'' Baffert said. ``If I ran him, and he got pneumonia or
something like that, I couldn't live with myself.''
</P>
<P>
   According to Baffert, he suspected something was amiss when
Silver Charm did not eat his entire morning meal.
</P>
<P>
   ``He usually dives right into the bucket,'' Baffert said.
Referring to Rudy Silva, he added: ``His groom said he didn't even
go for the grain. He said he went right to the corner and just put
his head down.''
</P>
<P>
   Baffert did not know when Silver Charm would be able to resume
training or race again.
</P>
<P>
   This is the second time in less than four months that a minor
setback has kept Silver Charm out of a major race. In March, he
bruised a foot on the eve of the Santa Anita Handicap and was
scratched. Three weeks later, however, he was flown halfway around
the world and won the $4 million Dubai World Cup.
</P>
<P>
   In his only start since then, Silver Charm was upset as the
odds-on favorite in the Stephen Foster Handicap at Churchill Downs
on June 13.
</P>
<P>
   Entries for the Gold Cup will be taken Thursday morning. Skip
Away is scheduled to arrive at Hollywood Park Thursday after a
flight from New York. Gary Stevens, who had been scheduled to ride
Silver Charm, has regained the mount on Gentlemen. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
