6-24 -- For many young people, a computer job paying from $30,000
to $60,000 a year seems far more appealing than pursuing a degree
whose value is unclear. ``A degree is just a piece of paper with a
gold stamp on it,'' says Jonah Blossom, 20, who left Santa Barbara
City College after one year to take a full time $30,000-a-year job
