   University of Houston organic chemistry professor Randall Lee
confirmed that napalm is as safe as gasoline.
</P>
<P>
   GNI's Reeves said the public outcry in Indiana was caused by
inflammatory media accounts complete with Vietnam-era footage of
napalm exploding.
</P>
<P>
   ``There was a lack of communication, and there was some
politics, and all of a sudden everything was inflamed,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   But worries about safety persist.
</P>
<P>
   ``This has not been handled well at all,'' said Bentsen. ``They
need to come out and make a statement about how they are proposing
to do this and give the public a chance to respond.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
